cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CR 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning, specifically with the ability of neural networks to learn logical entailment relations between expressions. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves experimentation with different neural network architectures, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves the use of an automatic theorem prover, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
